# @haku Editor UI

Docs: `docs/ui-kit.md` · Failures: `docs/edge-cases.md`

## Mutations

All scene changes → `commitSceneEdit` in `commands/scene-history.ts`. Never mutate `world` / `sceneDocument` in store directly.

## Reuse (do not rebuild)

| Need | Component |
| ---- | --------- |
| Numbers | `NumberField` + `DraggableNumberLabel` |
| Simple component | `SchemaFields` |
| Material | `MaterialPropertiesPanel` |
| Section wrapper | `InspectorComponentSection` |
| Layout | `EditorLayout` + `react-resizable-panels` |
| Dialog pattern | `RenderSettingsDialog`, `ModelPickerDialog` |

## React / state

- `memo()` on panels; narrow Zustand selectors
- **Never** put Three.js objects in React state
- `Engine` created once in `ViewportPanel` `useEffect`; edits → `engine.setWorld(world)`
- Viewport gizmos: `packages/editor/src/viewport/` only

## CSS

Co-located `*.css` — classes `haku-*`, `mesh-field*`, `menu-bar*`. Match tokens in `docs/ui-kit.md`.

## Empty states

Every panel/dialog needs explicit empty copy (e.g. `Select an entity`, `No model assets in project`).
